33-25 Irving Place, and 116-14 East 16th Street, at and adjoining the S.W. corner, buildings about to be demolished to make room for two 12-story office buildings. The corner one will later be known as the Nemo Building. 112-10-0B East 16th Street, also shown here, will remain.
March, 1909.
Brown Brothers.
